      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DHAULAGIRI NZ (5) drew on the back row and raced parked before drawing clear for an impressive win at Listed level in the Port Pirie Cup a week ago, cruising home by 16 metres. Has a great record at this circuit and distance with two wins and a placing from three attempts. The one to beat. HEZA PUNK ROCKER NZ (8) did some work to find the front before fading out of the Port Pirie Cup as favourite last week. He is much better than that, winning the Victor Harbor Cup prior. He strikes at 50 per cent at this distance and draws for a trail. Could bounce back. LAST TANGO IN HEAVEN NZ (9) added to his good form when he chased Dhaulagiri for third in the Port Pirie Cup. Winner at Gawler prior and races well at this circuit and distance. LORD ZARIAS NZ (7) will be fitter for recent racing and can be competitive if things go his way from a wide draw.",
